0>(7/26/01 6:33:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pickup group pro and con</span><hr size=1> what is your experience with pickup groups ?<br>
good ?<br>
bad ?<br>
no opinion ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujableakl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jableakl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/01 6:36:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickup group pro and con</span><hr size=1> At one time I found them to be real good. But that was a time when I was well ahead of the HP Curve and the higher lvl zones were less populated and more dangerous. Players had to be more in tune with what was going on around them. Not to say there are not good players out there cause there are but for the most part I find pick up groups to be less effective as they use to be. Oh well, part of it could be I am just sick of the xp grind and enjoy raiding and working on other goals instead now that I am full xp 60 <p>Cuthbert Dirgewielder
El Virtuoso and Uber Geek
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax Sceleris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/01 7:08:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickup group pro and con</span><hr size=1> The state of the &quot;higher level&quot; pickup group is worsening.  A lot of good players have done all of the XP grinding they're ever gonna do and a lot of &quot;bozos with time to kill&quot; are getting higher and higher level.<br>
<br>
The only people left in places where there are pickup groups are people who still seek ph@t l3wtz.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulierre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lierre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/01 7:30:37 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickup group pro and con</span><hr size=1> I hate pickup groups with a passion.  I have had a few that are not so bad, though.  Very few . . . . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umeganthistletoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Megan Thistletoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/01 8:11:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickup group pro and con</span><hr size=1> Groups are generally what you make of them. If you decide to create a pickup group and you find a class that does something you don't like then let them know. <br>
<br>
Communication is generally the key in any good group no matter if it's pickup or a guild raid. I tell people all the time, you're on snares, you're on heals, you're backup healer so easy on the nukes, make sure you load evac, etc. The key is to use tact when you deal with people and not automatically assume since this class blows all their mana or that class doesn't taunt off the healers that they suck and should be removed. Instead let them know their role in the group straight away, let them know what the group is there for, (exp, need before greed, a certain item, etc.). If you take a minute and teach one person &quot;your way&quot; of grinding then they just may learn and make another pickup group very happy. Some people seem to be hopeless cases and have an extreme learning problems or attention spans. If you can get through to these people by sending them a tell saying that this person needs to do his job or be removed from the group then they might get a clue. <br>
<br>
People are too quick to bitch about something without taking the time to teach.<br>
Of course there are many more facets that I haven't covered here and there are extreme cases for everything, but I hope you are mature enough to understand what I'm driving at. <p><p><font color="#008000" face="Arial"><b>Megan Thistletoe</b></font></p>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujableakl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jableakl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/01 8:46:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickup group pro and con</span><hr size=1> Although in a utopian world that may happen Megan, the truth be told, most groups are able enough. But without fail it seems that everytime the group get goin someone wants to alter what is going on or wants to pull things that are not part of the plan. Usually resulting in death.<br>
<br>
For example. Have a decent group goin, it is not a stellar group but decent fighting in Sebilis &lt;ugh&gt;. Anyway lets say we are down at D1 in the bug room off to the right, spawn is broken and everyone so far has stated they are just interested in xp and are content with killing what can be handled. The group has the camp under control and are able to take some down time for medding when needed. This is going along great and the xp is doin ok. All of sudden on member or a new member you just got down there starts whining they want to take on more. At first the group says to the person that they are happy with what is goin on and feel that taking on more mobs is just not within the capabilities of the group. Without fail after a while 1 of 2 things happen. <br>
1) They leave the group &lt;YAY&gt;<br>
2) They start pulling extra out of D2 and low and behold the rest of the group was right. It could not be handled, Evac or CR either way it is a pain in the ass. To make things worse then this person starts blaming ppl for not being able to handle it or leaves. If they leave YAY. Either way, now we have to break back down into the room if we decide to go back. Usually the group breaks up and the great time that was happening comes to an end.<br>
<br>
Greedy people are the problem or hyper people. Another situation is you get into the zone and being a bard this has happened a lot to me. A group says man you are the last guy we need and we can move. So join the group and ask what are we goin for? They say Ilis Frog Jail. I say Cool. before we start working down and I find out I am the only one in the group over lvl 55. So I ask, are you sure we can do this? I mean we have no shaman or chanter to slow and we are bit low on level. They start saying how they can do it. I use to head down and give it a try but now I would just disband. <br>
<br>
Hyper person is that guy who is never happy enough with how fast the kills are goin and starts pulling when you already have an assigned puller. I just disband these people any more if I am the leader. <br>
<br>
This happens more times than I care to even think about any more and this is just the easy to see problems. Get some of the people that lurk in seb down there sometime when there is like only 12 people in the zone and watch how the screw things up so badly it is unbelievable. They are so use to the entire zone spawn rate being broken that they are not sure how to deal with a full pop. You can see better evidence of this in Chardok sometime.<br>
<br>
Anyway you can talk to them til you are blue in the face but they just dont seem to listen.<br>
<br>
oh well have fun<br>
