Phantasmist Cazic Thule<br>
<url>http://www.elementofdarkness.com<url> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umerauk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merauk</A> at: 7/26/01 10:09:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umokasstardust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mokas Stardust</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/01 11:24:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickup group pro and con</span><hr size=1> I love pickup groups. Isn't it the whole idea of the game to go out and be social and play with the other little critters? Having to interact with strangers is part of the game and is exactly how you make new friends and alliances. People who keep to themselves and their guild are, perhaps enjoying the game in their own way, but as for me I like to group with new people. I hate that a lot of the higher level dungeons are &quot;bring your own group&quot; and all. <br>
<br>
There are, of course, problems. There are the occasional assholes, the &quot;ebays&quot; who don't know what they're doing, the quiet groups in which no one says a word - just working like clockwork like its a 9-5 job, the loot issues, etc. But these things happen. You just learn to adapt and fix whatever problems there are. <br>
<br>
Ah well... I am an adamant pick-up group lover. Wish there were more 50s~ish pick-up group dungeons, besides Karnors...<br>
<br>
~Mokas~<br>
 52 Bard<br>
Exiled Alliance<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uvibesjoker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ViBeSJoKeR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/27/01 10:32:45 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.jollyjokers.com/vibes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickup group pro and con</span><hr size=1> Oh I love the Quiet groups, cause you know this group will succeed in killing everything and not having 1 issue where they panic or whatever, and when the group finally has to leave all are very respectfull greet you and everyone admires the quality of the others.<br>
Not a single word was spoken we all got our exp and items, no loot issues have occured and then like 3 days later when u are bored in god knows where, you get the tell hey man wanna group!<br>
<br>
Those are the groups that go all the way cause they know their tasks and duties without speaking a single word.<br>
<br>
