<font size="-1">Beauty of whatever kind, in its supreme development, invariably excites the sensitive soul to tears.</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utreistaania.showPublicProfile?language=EN>treistaania</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/27/01 12:21:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> i love it</span><hr size=1> actually i usually play in a semi pickup group, that is i group with RL friends and we add people we find interesting to be around.. not that we need that extra shaman all the times or perhaps the necro that we really didnt have a use for... the bottom line is i play the game to have fun and meet interesting people and the game itself is secondary for me.. when people group with us you can usually tell after a few minutes if they are FIT for the job or not.. that translates to if they can stand our humor and sarcasm.<br>
you have to grind exp at times and damn it is boring.. so there has actually been times when we have created situations by purpose to spice the camp up... like pull way to many and see how many can make it out alive and things like that.. another fun thing is to use the AE dots alot when you have a chanter... damn they are fun to see when they run around like crazy to mez them..<br>
the fun part of this is that we generally can handle the situation and there are rarely deaths in our groups but we do have alot of fun and no one knows what to expect and it dont get boring.<br>
we have had several comments like<br>
&quot;you guys do things in a strange way but it works ive gotten 2 yellow bubs in less then 4 hours&quot;<br>
in Lguk its hilarious to pull king to lord and vice versa..<br>
but remember that you are responsible for you actions and dont have fun at some other groups expence, that is do not pull dangerous stunts around others that arent part of the plan.<br>
<br>
Sebilis is the most boring place in eq..<br>
try some other places like HS, explore and try to do a wing with as few as possible, or replace the chanter with a shaman or perhaps a ranger..<br>
all to add some challenge to the game.<br>
this is also why i quit my chanter and made an SK, chanter ALWAYS gets a group and its not a very hard class to play.. everyone takes care of you as a chanter, while they couldnt care less if your an SK.<br>
maybe i play the game for all the wrong reasons but after 2 years this is how i get my kicks..<br>
<br>
p/s<br>
most fun class ive played so far is shaman.. but never play it as slow/buff only... play it activly and they are hellafun...<br>
