Darka -32 wiz first char and has 120 sta- forgotten(how was i to know wizards used INT) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mr Who needs a title?!</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/27/01 5:39:26 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i love it</span><hr size=1> If I'm going to do pick up, that's the way I would rather have it done.  Add to a group of friends (even if that group is only one or two more).  At least I know there are people there I can count on.<br>
<br>
I don't care for pick up, but I will do them if I don't have other alternatives.  The last one I did was in KC a couple nights ago (which is now surprisingly empty) while on my Enchanter.  It started out a bit rocky when we invited two Clerics  One thought we were thinking she couldn't handle the heals.  The rest of the group was thinking this was a good opportunity to allow the Clerics to nuke and/or stun (or swap on this role to give them each a break).  *shrug*  When she left we added a Ranger and just started cleaning up.  It was great.<br>
<br>
The pick up group before that sucked.  People sitting back and putting in minimal effort.  I had to work twice as hard to make up for two shitty Paladins.  Add in people quitting out for no reason and it was not a good experience.  *shrug*<br>
<br>
I prefer guild groups.  If I need to do pick up, I will.  If it sucks, I'll either find something else to do or make the best of it. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/27/01 5:47:56 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.one.se/users/chribesk/edeina.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i love it</span><hr size=1> I used to love pickupgroups in Lower Guk. When I started poking around in Karnor's and Sebilis I instead turned to hate it. Group screwed up too much, broke up and sometimes left you with a unressed and fully equipped corpse deep in the dungeon.<br>
